# Git workflow

## Branches

- **Base branch:** `main` only — no `develop`
- **Naming:** `feature/`, `fix/`, `chore/`, `docs/` + short kebab-case slug
- **One branch = one PR** with a clear scope

## Before opening a PR

```powershell
git fetch origin
git rebase origin/main   # or merge origin/main
pnpm typecheck; pnpm lint
cd src-tauri; cargo fmt --check; cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings; cargo test
```

## Commits

- Imperative subject, optional scope: `feat(dictation): add pause presets`
- Types: `feat`, `fix`, `chore`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `ci`
- Do not commit secrets (`.tauri/calliop.key`, `.env`)

## Releases

- Tag on `main`: `v0.1.x` triggers release workflow
- Version bumps in `package.json`, `src-tauri/Cargo.toml`, `src-tauri/tauri.conf.json`, `releases/v{x}.md`

## Protected `main`

- Merge via PR (admin bypass allowed for maintainers)
- Required CI: `frontend`, `rust`
- No force-push or branch deletion on `main`

Full details: `docs/branch-strategy.md`
